<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language>英文</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 13:47:49 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Spotify is laying off 200 employees from its podcast division]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Spotify <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-will-lay-off-6-percent-of-employees-130337498.html">今年的裁员</a>并未结束。作为“战略调整”的一部分，该公司正在其播客部门<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://newsroom.spotify.com/2023-06-05/an-update-on-changes-to-spotifys-podcast-business-june-2023/">裁员</a>200 人，约占其员工总数的 2%。 Spotify 正在转向一种更“量身定制的方法”，为每个播客创作者和他们的节目优化资源，流媒体服务认为这需要一个更精简的团队。</p><p>新战略还将看到 Spotify 将其<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-dropping-the-paywall-for-some-gimlet-podcasts-162547473.html">Gimlet</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-03-26-spotify-original-podcasts-parcast.html">Parcast</a>制作公司合并为一个更新的 Spotify Studios 部门。他们将继续制作广为人知的原创作品并开始新的节目，尽管将​​重新强调能够培养大量观众的频繁出现的内容。整个 Spotify 将致力于“最大化现有观众的消费”，鼓励他们更频繁地收听和收听更多播客。该公司还在发展其 Spotify For Podcasters 分析，改进其广告选项并添加“更多商业模式”以帮助创作者获利​​。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>自 2019 年开始大力投资播客以来，这家提供商热衷于宣传其增长，包括收购 Gimlet、Parcast 和<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-12-23-spotify-year-in-podcasts-2019.html">创作者平台 Anchor</a> 。它现在声称是地球“大多数角落”最受欢迎的播客平台，拥有超过 1 亿听众和 500 万节目。 Spotify 表示，使用量增长了 1,400% 以上。它还说它是美国最大的出版商。</p><p>即便如此，裁员给公司增加了一系列打击。据报道，Spotify 去年秋天<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-cancels-some-original-podcasts-134405125.html">取消了许多节目</a>，在此过程中裁掉了近 5% 的播客团队。该服务还在 1 月份解雇了 6% 的员工，首席内容官 Dawn Ostroff（因播客内容增长 40 倍而受到赞誉）同时辞职。内容本身也存在困难，包括 Spotify 独家<em>The Joe Rogan Experience</em>的<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-joe-rogan-deal-value-podcast-205637664.html">错误信息问题</a>。该公司可能是该类别中的强者，但它不再像以前那样安全。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-laying-off-200-employees-from-its-podcast-division-134749721.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-laying-off-200-employees-from-its-podcast-division-134749721.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 732b24f5-5368-4e06-ab81-339e3a5fd14e</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 13:47:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685972869</ingested><modified> 2023-06-05T13:47:58+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="2424" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-02/25293fe0-8f87-11ec-adda-f9ec1ab41fca" width="4000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2424" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-02/25293fe0-8f87-11ec-adda-f9ec1ab41fca" width="4000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[